radiographic_examinations.findings: The lower chest is unremarkable. The liver enhances homogeneously and is without focal abnormality. The gallbladder and biliary tree appear normal. The pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands appear normal. The kidneys enhance normally and excrete contrast symmetrically. The stomach, duodenum, and abdominal loops of small and large bowel are of normal caliber, without wall thickening, or associated mass. The appendix is hyperemic, dilated to 10 mm, features mural edema, and surrounding fat stranding. There is a small amount of minimally complex free fluid tracking into the pelvis. There is no fluid collection. There is no pneumoperitoneum. The portal, splenic, and mesenteric veins are patent. The abdominal aorta is not enlarged and its main branches are patent. There is no retroperitoneal, periportal, or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. The rectum and sigmoid are normal. There is minimal diffuse bladder wall thickening. The uterus and ovaries are normal. There is no pelvic mass. There is no pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy. There are no lytic or sclerotic osseous lesions concerning for malignancy.
